</tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;">
<td style="display:block; font-size:1em; height:10.7em; padding:0px;">
<div class="gallerytext" style="height:10.6em; width:167px; line-height:1.3em; padding:2px 6px 1px 6px; overflow-y:auto; margin:0px; border:none; border-width:0px;">Plate 59: <i>De qué sirve una taza?</i> (<i>What good is a cup?</i>) Two starving women lie on the ground, one near death while a third kneels by their side and offers a cup to the dying woman. &#160;</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<table style="width:180px; float:left; border-collapse:collapse; margin:3px;">
<tr>
<td style="height:140px; border:1px solid #CCCCCC; background-color:#F8F8F8; padding:0px; text-align:center">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Goya-Guerra_(60).jpg" class="image" title="Plate 60: No hay quien los socorra (There is no one to help them) On a hillside three women lie dead, and a lone figure weeps in mournful grief."><img alt="On a lonely hillside three women lie dead, while a lone figure weeps in mournful grief." src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Goya-Guerra_(60).jpg/160px-Goya-Guerra_(60).jpg" width="160" height="115" class="thumbborder" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Goya-Guerra_%2860%29.jpg/240px-Goya-Guerra_%2860%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Goya-Guerra_%2860%29.jpg/320px-Goya-Guerra_%2860%29.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;">
<td style="display:block; font-size:1em; height:10.7em; padding:0px;">
<div class="gallerytext" style="height:10.6em; width:167px; line-height:1.3em; padding:2px 6px 1px 6px; overflow-y:auto; margin:0px; border:none; border-width:0px;">Plate 60: <i>No hay quien los socorra</i> (<i>There is no one to help them</i>) On a hillside three women lie dead, and a lone figure weeps in mournful grief. &#160;</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<table style="width:180px; float:left; border-collapse:collapse; margin:3px;">
<tr>
<td style="height:140px; border:1px solid #CCCCCC; background-color:#F8F8F8; padding:0px; text-align:center">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Goya-Guerra_(62).jpg" class="image" title="Plate 62: Las camas de la muerte (The beds of death) A woman walks past dozens of wrapped bodies awaiting burial."><img alt="A woman walks from right to left, past dozens of bodies awaiting burial. Her face and body are covered with a protective shawl." src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Goya-Guerra_(62).jpg/160px-Goya-Guerra_(62).jpg" width="160" height="115" class="thumbborder" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Goya-Guerra_%2862%29.jpg/240px-Goya-Guerra_%2862%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Goya-Guerra_%2862%29.jpg/320px-Goya-Guerra_%2862%29.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;">
<td style="display:block; font-size:1em; height:10.7em; padding:0px;">
<div class="gallerytext" style="height:10.6em; width:167px; line-height:1.3em; padding:2px 6px 1px 6px; overflow-y:auto; margin:0px; border:none; border-width:0px;">Plate 62: <i>Las camas de la muerte</i> (<i>The beds of death</i>) A woman walks past dozens of wrapped bodies awaiting burial. &#160;</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The second group, plates 48 to 64, detail the effects of the famine which ravaged Madrid from August 1811 until after <a href="Arthur_Wellesley,_1st_Duke_of_Wellington" title="Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington">Wellington</a>'s armies liberated the city in August 1812. Starvation killed 20,000 people in the city that year.<sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34"><span>[</span>31<span>]</span></a></sup> In these plates, Goya's focus is directed away from the generalised scenes of slaughter of anonymous, unaligned people in unnamed regions of Spain; he turns towards a specific horror unfolding in Madrid. The famine was a result of many factors. For example, French invaders and Spanish guerrillas and bandits blocked paths and roads into the city, hampering the provision of food.</p>
<p>Goya does not focus on the reasons for the shortage, nor does he apportion blame to any one party. Instead, he is concerned only with its effect on the population.<sup id="cite_ref-H297_35-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-H297-35"><span>[</span>32<span>]</span></a></sup> Although the images in the group were based on the experience of Madrid, none of the scenes depict specific events, and there are no identifiable buildings to place the scenes. Goya's focus is on the darkened masses of dead and barely alive bodies, men carrying corpses of women, and bereaved children mourning for lost parents.<sup id="cite_ref-36" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-36"><span>[</span>33<span>]</span></a></sup> Hughes believes <a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Goya-Guerra_(50).jpg" class="extiw" title="commons:File:Goya-Guerra (50).jpg">plate 50</a>, <i>Madre infeliz!</i> (<i>Unhappy mother!</i>), to be the most powerful and poignant of the group. He suggests that the space between the small girl sobbing and the corpse of her mother represents "a darkness that seems to be the very essence of loss and orphanhood".<sup id="cite_ref-Hughes_2004.2C_299_37-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Hughes_2004.2C_299-37"><span>[</span>34<span>]</span></a></sup> This group of plates was probably completed by early 1814.<sup id="cite_ref-38" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-38"><span>[</span>35<span>]</span></a></sup> A scarcity of materials during the famine may have accounted for the freer application of <a href="Aquatint" title="Aquatint">aquatint</a> in these prints; Goya was sometimes forced to use defective plates or reuse old plates after they were <a href="Burnish" title="Burnish">burnished</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-S129_4-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-S129-4"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=The_Disasters_of_War&action=edit&section=5.php.html" title="Edit section: Bourbons and clergy">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Bourbons_and_clergy">Bourbons and clergy</span></h3>
<table style="background:transparent; border:1px solid #f0f0f0; margin-top:0.5em;">
<tr>
<td>
<table style="width:180px; float:left; border-collapse:collapse; margin:3px;">
